{
  "texts": [
    "Kaushal et al. (2018) presents a comprehensive review of ODT approaches including evolutionary algorithms, conventional neural networks and feed-forward neural networks (FNNs).",
    "It is shown that there are suitable approaches for almost any combination of known visual constraints.",
    "For example, FNNs are most successful for video streams with irregular illumination change and noise, whilst darker hues and low frame rate are best handled by DL-based CNN classifiers.",
    "Within IC we find two distinct paradigms, (1) singular target ODT and (2) multiple target ODT.",
    "(1) is much easier to solve and solutions tend to use YOLO detection."
  ]
}